  "These bacteria do not need energy because they are at equilibrium": "",
  "Chemosynthetic bacteria oxidize inorganic compounds (like H₂S) in exergonic reactions that release free energy, which is used to produce ATP and fix carbon. They obey both laws: energy is transformed (first law) and entropy increases (second law).": "",
  "A cell biologist argues that living organisms appear to violate the second law of thermodynamics because they maintain highly ordered structures. How would a physicist respond to this apparent contradiction?": "",
  "Organisms are open systems that decrease local entropy by increasing entropy in their surroundings (releasing heat, CO₂, waste); the total entropy of the universe still increases": "",
