  "Organisms create energy to maintain order, violating the first law instead": "",
  "The second law only applies to non-living systems": "",
  "Living organisms are open systems that exchange matter and energy with their environment. They maintain internal order (low entropy) by increasing environmental entropy (heat, waste). The total entropy of organism + surroundings always increases.": "",
