  "It is stored as potential energy for later use within the broader context of energy analysis": "",
  "Approximately 75% of energy from ATP hydrolysis in muscles is released as heat, with only ~25% converted to mechanical work. This is consistent with the second law: no energy conversion is 100% efficient, and the lost energy increases entropy as heat.": "",
  "A biochemist studying metabolic regulation notices that when cells have abundant ATP, catabolic pathways slow down. When ATP levels drop and ADP/AMP rise, catabolism accelerates. What principle of energy management does this illustrate?": "",
  "Random fluctuation in enzyme activity when the interaction between energy and catabolic factors is taken into full account": "",
