  "Energy is only transferred between organisms of the same species, despite what intuition might initially suggest": "",
  "The 10% rule reflects thermodynamic constraints: organisms metabolize ~90% of ingested energy for cellular respiration (losing it as heat to entropy), excretion, and non-digestible matter. Only ~10% is incorporated into biomass available to the next trophic level.": ""
